    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said that at the meeting of the American Jewish Library Association.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And a woman who survived a camp got up, very angry, and she said, I don't feel any guilt.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, well, I do.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I do.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's not a sense of guilt that I've done something wrong, but it's a sense of, why am I here and others are not.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Like this little boy said, maybe God had a purpose.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
